  "prompt": "How can I get Scrum Master certification?",
  "response": "To get a Scrum Master certification, you have several options:\n\n1. Professional Scrum Master (PSM) Certification\n- Offered by Scrum.org\n- Multiple levels: PSM I, II, III\n- Online exam\n- Study materials available\n- No mandatory training required\n\n2. Certified ScrumMaster (CSM)\n- Offered by Scrum Alliance\n- Requires 2-day training course\n- Exam after training\n- More popular and widely recognized\n- Annual renewal required\n\n3. SAFe Scrum Master\n- Scaled Agile Framework certification\n- Focuses on enterprise-level Scrum\n- Requires training and exam\n- More advanced/comprehensive\n\nSteps to get certified:\n1. Choose a certification path\n2. Study Scrum principles\n3. Take recommended training\n4. Prepare for the exam\n5. Take certification test\n6. Maintain certification (if required)\n\nRecommended preparation:\n- Read \"Scrum Guide\"\n- Take online practice tests\n- Study Agile/Scrum methodology\n- Consider online courses\n- Join Scrum communities\n\nAverage costs:\n- PSM: $150-$250\n- CSM: $300-$600\n- SAFe: $700-$1000",
